Notes on `basics'

* This file last updated on 7 Feb.
* All source files checked for possible dangers, and appropriate warnings
  included here. (7 Feb)

1. BBox: contains classes Point and BBox

1.1 Point
  constr.: Point(x,y)
  methods: int x(), y()
  warning: -

1.2 Area
  constr.: Area(w,h), Area(wh)
  methods: int w(), h()
  warning: -

1.3 BBox
  constr.: BBox(lx,ty,rx,by), BBox(Point,Area), BBox()
  methods: |= &= & (bbox); 
           bool empty(), intersect(bbox), contains(x,y), contains(pt);
	   int left(), top(), right(), bottom(), width(), height();
	   Point topleft(); Area area();
	   addmargin(l,t,r,b), moveto(x,y), moveto(Point),
	   resize(w,h), resize(Area)
  warning: construction and resize() may leave r<l or b<t. Use empty() to
	   test for emptyness before assuming +ve area.

2. Byte: class Byte = unsigned char
   warning: -

3. Filename: filename representation
   constr.: Filename(string fn), ()
   methods: +=(string/char*), addsuffix(string/char*);
	    char *name(); bool exist(bool cdir)
   notes:   +=() adds an OS-dependent directory separator (UNIX: `/')
            addsuffix() adds an OS-dependent suffix separator (UNIX: `.')
   warning: exist(true) tries to create the containing directory if the
	    file doesn't exist. There is no guarantee that this succeeds:
	    errors in mkdir() remain unreported.

4. Infty: defines INFTY=10^8
   warning: INFTY != MAXINT 

5. KeyCode: class TKeyCode = short int
   warning: -

6. Throw: defines fthrow, tthrow and athrow
   note:    Use of athrow() is recommended, because it writes the message
	    to stderr before continuing. This avoids losing error messages
	    in the case of throw before exception caught.
   warning: -

7. Word: class Word = 32 bits unsigned
   warning: This is impl.dep. Current vsn uses unsigned long and doesn't
	    explicitly check its size.

8. dbx: void dbx(lvl,fmt,...): Debug output, printf style.
	lvl = priority; 0=extreme, 1=almost toplevel, 4=happens every poll
   warning: -

9. getline:
   : string getline_nocmt(istream): Reads one line from an istream
	into a string, skipping any empty lines, and lines starting with
	any of [%#!;/]. Returns "" on eof only.
   : skipwhite(istream): Skips spaces and tabs, but not newlines
	on istream.
   : skipcmt(istream): Skips commentary lines
   : skiptoeol(istream): Skips upto and incl. next eol
   warning: -

10. stringtok: class stringtok
   constr.: stringtok(string), ()
   methods: =(string): resets.
	    string token(char delim/char *delims)
   notes:   cf. strtok, but for class string.
            token() returns "" if there are no more tokens.
   warning: Avoid inf. loop at end of string

11. timetest: class TimeTest
   constr.: TimeTest()
   methods: reset(), print()
   note: For testing purposes

12. vecio: stream operators on vectors
   : ostream << vector<T>
   : istream >> vector<T>
   : string >> vector<T>
   warning: - Elements must be <whitespace> separated on the istream.
	    - operator>>(istream,T) must exist.
	    - The data is APPENDED to the vector.
